The paper proposes a deep RL algorithm for value function estimation, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence research (cs.LG, cs.AI). The algorithm involves predicting future trajectories and returns, which are relevant to robotics and control (cs.RO). The paper also uses convolutional neural networks for trajectory representation, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper's evaluation is based on continuous control tasks, which are relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
